# 🎧 GRC & Me – Episode 2: The Father of GRC

## 🎙️ Episode Info
- **Podcast Title:** GRC & Me  
- **Episode Title:** The Father of GRC  
- **Guest:** Michael Rasmussen (GRC 20/20)  
- **Date Listened:** July 23, 2025  
- **Link:** [Listen on LogicGate](https://podcast.logicgate.com/public/30/GRC-%26-Me-d0046b6b/d3a035ef)

---

## 🔑 Key Topics Discussed
1. Michael Rasmussen's definition of GRC as a capability, not a tool  
2. How governance is often overlooked in GRC programs  
3. The importance of integrating strategy, risk, and compliance holistically  
4. The rise of privacy as a key GRC driver due to data breaches  

---

## 🧠 Takeaways / Lessons Learned
- GRC is about aligning **objectives**, **risk**, and **integrity**  
- Tools should support a strategy—not define one  
- Governance is the **“G” in GRC**—not just an afterthought  
- Consumers increasingly demand better privacy governance  

---

## 📌 RMF Process Insights

| RMF Step       | Insight from Episode                                           |
|----------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Prepare**    | Align risk efforts to business mission and values first        |
| **Categorize** | Use a strategic lens when defining impact levels               |
| **Select**     | Choose controls that support both compliance and mission needs |
| **Implement**  | Ensure governance policies support control implementation      |
| **Assess**     | Validate that controls are meaningful, not just in place       |
| **Authorize**  | Link risk decisions to mission-critical objectives             |
| **Monitor**    | Track business-aligned metrics, not just technical ones        |

