## 📘 OCEG GRC Capability Model – Overview

The **OCEG GRC Capability Model** is a globally recognized framework designed to help organizations integrate Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) into a unified, effective capability.

> ✅ **Purpose:** To enable organizations to reliably achieve objectives, address uncertainty, and act with integrity.

---

## 🔑 Core Objectives

- Align GRC activities with **organizational strategy**
- Break down silos between risk, compliance, audit, and ethics
- Establish a repeatable process to manage obligations and performance
- Guide organizations toward **continuous improvement** of GRC capabilities

---

## 🧱 GRC Capability Components (The GRC Wheel)

| Phase   | Description                                                                    |
|---------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Learn**   | Understand internal and external context: stakeholders, risks, obligations |
| **Align**   | Set governance structures, roles, culture, and objectives                  | 
| **Perform** | Implement controls, processes, and procedures to meet goals                |
| **Review**  | Monitor performance and compliance; improve processes continuously         |

---

## 📚 Why It Matters

- Promotes **integration** of risk, compliance, security, ethics, and audit  
- Focuses on **value-driven GRC** instead of checkbox compliance  
- Enhances alignment with frameworks like **NIST RMF, ISO 31000, COSO ERM**, etc.  
- Helps mature your GRC program in a scalable, adaptable way

---

